				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Rhasin you don't get it, we are talking about a snare not to help us be needed in groups, but to solo again as we use to. A snare would help us regain our solo ability. We are not talking about how it effects our desirability in a group. The magician class has always been able to solo and with the release of pop that ability is not what it was, hence all these threads you are seeing about needing help to regain that which we lost. 
<br />

<br />
As for DPS in a group setting we are fine, in a raid setting we are lacking to a wizard as pets don't last and their DPS is not enough to offset 6000+ crits wizards are getting. We can not control aggro like that can, so I resort to rains that do a nice amount of damage with low aggro. I am not a wizard I can deal with my DPS being lower on a raid when my pet isn't up. However I do not like the fact I can not solo as I used to, and every other damn pet class in the game can. That is my issue, and many others. Compair classes that are simular. Beastlords and Necro's have powerful pets, not as strong as ours, but close enough that to deny us a snare or a root is no longer warranted in my opinoin and many others. You may agree or disagree, that is what the forum is all about. 
<br />

<br />
CLASS BALLANCE means to me that if the other pet classes can solo, and the mage class use to be able to solo, something is wrong when they still can in the higher tiers and mages can not. We are NOT, again repeat NOT talking about groupability when we talk a snare or a root, as other classes are better suited to doing that than we are, but when we would like to solo for any reason at all we need the tools to do it. 
<br />

<br />
Does that make it clearer? It is not about how a snare would make us the most wanted groupable class, in fact it would change that standing very little. It does give us back our ability to solo, and THAT is that we are talking about.
